         <abstract>
            <p>A finite element method for the solution of a scattering problem for the reduced wave equation is formulated and analyzed. The method involves a reformulation of the problem on a bounded domain with a nonlocal boundary condition. The space of trial functions includes piecewise polynomial functions and functions arising from spherical harmonics.</p>
